Custom upgrades include a royal decor of marble, onyx, granite, mosaics, medallions, corbels, crystal, Venetian plaster, plush imported carpets and many hardwoods. Shower with custom pressure balancing automatic water mixing system. 

This classical inspired home includes too many upgrades to list. Granite counter kitchen tops, gas and inductive electric cook top, wine and beverage cabinets, coffee machine and commercial grade gas crepe maker, solid maple cabinets and skylights. Heated floors in kitchen, Venetian ceilings in the living room and throughout the home. Natural marble stone tile finished walls with hand painted sculpted border moldings. Imported carpet and custom finishings and lighting. 400 square foot pond with 20 mature Koi. Space for 4 vehicles inside the gated grounds. Front and back yard upgrades include covered carport, backyard cover, outdoor kitchen, renovated back-porch, custom landscaping and so much more.

The following are new: copper plumbing, dual pane windows, interior and exterior paint, flooring, stainless appliances, custom kitchen & baths, walk-in closet, 5 1/2 inch premium moldings, garage door and opener, LED lighting, sod and sprinklers, high-end chrome fixtures and hardware, upgraded electrical and more. Wide open great room with endless possibilities. There is a dedicated laundry room off the kitchen and the family room opens to a backyard with numerous fruit trees, open space and the potential to add a pool or spa. Nestled on a tree-lined street amongst many other quality homes, close to shopping, beach, freeways to LA/OC and 2 blocks from Cubberley Elementary School. There is no other newly remodeled home in Long Beach with this size and these amenities in this price range.

Fall in love with this Beautifully Restored Long Beach Craftsman Home. The Historic Architectural Detail flows into each room and every nook and yet offers a seamless blend of current amenities including New HVAC, Upgraded Electrical Wiring and Panel, Upgraded Copper Plumbing. The kitchen has undergone a transformation with Fully Customized Cabinetry, Stylish Chopping Block Countertops and Brand New Stainless Steel Appliances. The Detached Garage has been partially finished and could be used as an Office or Media Room. Attend Concerts and Picnics in Rose Park just a few blocks away! Discover the Value in this home and it's close proximity to the Hip and Trendy So Cal Living Style! Don't miss out Your New Home Awaits

Beautiful Bluff Park reconstruction. So much attention to detail has been paid to the amazing reconstruction of this 1921 classic home. This home has been rebuilt from the frame up. Even the foundation has been re-encased. So you have new: plumbing, heating, electrical, tank-less water heater, dual glaze low-e custom wood windows, adobe tile roof and 5/8" drywall. Ceiling, walls and floor hae been fully insulated. Gorgeous kitchen has dark maple cabinets, an island with storage, an extra deep double Kohler sink and oil rubbed bronze Moen faucet and Silestone solid counter tops. The tiles throughout this home are a combination of handmade tiles from Pratt Larson and Walker Zanger and the deco pieces in the hall bath are 1920 vintage lead. The large formal dining room is serviced by a butler's panrty and is open to the nicely sized living room. The family room is open to the kitchen, and leads out to the redwood deck in the yard. Front and rear yards are either sprinklered or have a drip system for water efficiency. There are raised garden beds, a firepit and a whimsical meditation corner in the yard. The front steps have been rebuilt and are faced in custom hand painted Walker Zanger tiles. Too many details to list here. Click video reel to see floorplan

Panoramic Ocean Views are the Backdrop to this Seductively Modern Condo Located in Long Beach's Premier High-rise. Floor-to-ceiling windows showcase sunrises towards the beaches, views of the Marina and Catalina, and beautiful sunsets over the hills of Palo Verde. This unit reflects a taste for quality design and fine finishes. There are Venetian plaster walls, Wenge doors, ultra-white Italian kitchen cabinetry, state of the art fade lighting, whisper quiet Somfy automated window system on dual pane windows. The flooring is a beautiful limestone with walnut hardwood in the bedrooms. The unit comes with wine storage and a valuable 5' by 5' storage area on the parking level. West Ocean Towers have gorgeous lobbies, 24 hour concierge service and are community friendly. Amenities include two fitness centers, pool, spa and sauna, dry cleaning service, lounge with kitchen and tv, outdoor fireplace, BBQ for entertaining, media room, and game room. Within walking distance is downtown Long Beach with its many restaurants. Easily accessible and enjoyable is the beach bike path to lively Belmont Shore. Easy access to freeways to LA and Orange County.

Conveniently located in town with quick boat access to Charlotte Harbor close to Fisherman's Village - lovely neighborhood - circular driveway with elegant entrance - open floor plan, cathedral ceilings, with many glass sliders - Pool area is open without cage in a private lush landscape, boat lift with approx. 10-15 minute boat ride to Charlotte Harbor, split floor plan with large master bedroom & bath on one side of the house and 2 bedrooms & bath on the other side of the house allowing privacy for all - elegant formal dining area, casual eat in kitchen area or spacious outside dining.  Come home and enjoy this lifestyle!

Welcome to paradise! Situated in beautiful Port Charlotte Florida is this 2 bedroom, 2 bathroom waterfront home. Minutes from shopping, beaches, hospitals and historic downtown Punta Gorda. Soak up the sun as you relax on your screened in lanai overlooking your private view and breathtaking sunsets over the Haverhill Waterway. Home features a split floor plan, vaulted ceilings, inside utility and the interior has been freshly painted. The family/great room is just off of the dining room, so you can easily entertain while having access to your screened and covered back porch with fully collapsable sliders. This well maintained home has a newer 3 ton, 16 seer Daiken AC installed back in April of 2015, ceramic tile throughout, large utility shed provides ample storage and although the massive back yard is fenced, you still have a perfect view of your privacy canal out back. Here is your chance to own your piece of paradise before the new year!

GO COUNTRY! 20 Acres on Charlie Creek complete with a furnished camp house, riding/walking trails and a huge (30x60) pole barn.  The house has front and back porches, metal roof, cell signal repeater, propane for the stove and the water heater, a newer AC unit, security system and so much more.  Property is partially fenced.  Whether you're looking for a place to enjoy quiet, serene country evenings, ride ATV's, fish or canoe the creek, hunt or simply enjoy/photograph nature and the natural beauty of old Florida, you'll LOVE this place.  Fossil finding friends, Charlie Creek has a treasure for you as well.  Leave the stress of everyday life behind and regroup in this tranquil, rustic setting. No regrets and no worries here!

This 2,000+ square foot, well-maintained, one-owner classic home is looking for a new owner.  With so much to offer such as a very large family or game room, a split floor plan, a bright great room and a cozy kitchen designed for the creation of memories, you will be calling this house your "home" in no time at all.  Situated on a spacious corner lot in the desirable, conveniently located community of Charlotte Park.  Imagine the excitement of making this 1968 classic an updated, enviable retro retreat! Opportunities like this are rare; don't delay or this one will be gone!

Imagine the possibilities! Great fixer in the great community of Duarte. Two bedroom one bath home ready for first time buyers or family ready to down size. Picture window off living room with view of front yard. Pass through window from kitchen to living room. Light and bright kitchen with access to back yard. Bedrooms with built in storage. Converted garage into workshop or den. Full bathroom off hallway to bedrooms. Great leveled fenced lot. House sits within walking distance to elementary school. Perfectly situated near freeways and shopping. Come see the potential!
Located in a country setting and yet close to major roadway, minutes away from shopping, restaurants and medical offices.

Thinking about a Residential Office space? This property may be what you are seeking. See floor plan. Own, not only, a wonderfully renovated residential office building but become part of South Tampa's preservation history when you purchase 333 Plant Ave, the original Lowry House. Built by Sumter Lowry, one of Tampa's first presiding members of the Commission Government Club of Tampa, this structure has been carefully and beautifully restored to house 6 generous sized and airy offices, a conference room, a reception room, a large kitchen, renovated full and half baths, 2 office equipment/ file storage rooms, and an additional attached storage room(not heated). The reception area and conference room could be offices. An outside back stairway allows private entrance to 2 of the upstairs offices, and 2 front doorways allow additional entrances. There are 9parking spaces in the rear and 2 spaces out front. The wide wrap-around porch is a great place to take a break from your work tasks. The attention to detail during restoration has left many of the original features such as fire places, the wood trimmed staircase and doorways, and interior glass transoms. All offices have hardwood floors except for the carpeted reception room, conference room, and hallways. Currently occupied by tenants, this could be both your office and income property. Access to downtown, I-4 and I-275, and the Selmon Cross Town Expressway made this Hyde Park property a gateway location for your business or practice.

PRE-CONSTRUCTION- TO BE BUILT. Custom Estate Property unlike any other in Punta Gorda Isles.  The Bordeaux model with every upgrade specified to be built in addition to a second custom attached guest home with rental potential on two lots with both golf course and long water views. The main house has 3 bedrooms, 3 bathrooms & a den with 2472 square feet of stunning living space. Enter through the palatial double doors into the spacious foyer that connects to the great room with tray ceilings. Your view travels to the gourmet kitchen and onto the lanai with zero corner sliders that open for another 568 square feet of space on the lanai and summer kitchen. The master suite has impressive views of the infinity edge spa and golf course beyond, as well as a spa-quality bathroom with separate shower and tub and his and hers closets with dressing room. The additional two guest rooms each have their own unique bathrooms with incredible design details showing elegance. Having a flexible space such as an office or den in addition to the three bedrooms makes for a fabulous convenience, also overlooking the pool and ultimately the lush green at St. Andrews South Golf Course. Saving the best for last, the gourmet kitchen with impressive island and breakfast bar is the gathering spot for entertaining.  Around the driveway is an 1128 sq.ft. guest home with a gourmet kitchen, game room and family room, guest bedroom and bathroom, and two car garage.  The outdoor shower and wrap-around porch complete the second residence.

French doors lead out into a well-manicured yard measuring over 6,500 square feet. The spacious fenced lot has a paved patio area tucked into a shady corner of the well-manicured lawn, the perfect spot to sit and relax after a busy day. The upstairs unit can be accessed via two separate entrances and features two bedrooms, one bath, a formal dining room, a quaint kitchen and an airy living room with a cheery picture window. The delightful sun room is the perfect place to enjoy your morning coffee and a grapefruit picked fresh from your own yard. Located near Cal State Long Beach, Long Beach City Beach, various parks, and waterways will make living in one unit and renting the other a breeze.

Some wood laminate floors. Copper plumbing. Composition shingle roof. One bedroom has wood paneling and uses converted attic space as a closet. Would make a nice study and still have 4 bedrooms. Large living room with fireplace and sliding glass door opens to 2 covered patios. Private backyard. Fruit tree and roses. Desirable El Dorado Park Estates. New Newcomb Academy K-8 Elementary school. Conveniently located near park, golf course, shopping, dining, and freeway. Although built in 1966, this home is immaculate. There is nothing like it on the market!
